dataIdInfo.idPurp: This data was compiled to provide demographic information for use in Title VI compliance analysis.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This is the 20165 update to the ALPACA planning tool. US Census 5-year American Community Survey (ACS) (2012-2016) data tables (B01001, B16004, B17021, B18101, B18102, B18103, B18104, B18105, B18106, B18107, B19013, B21001, C02003) were acquired from American FactFinder (https://factfinder.census.gov/). This data was compiled to provide demographic information for use in Title VI compliance analysis and WSDOT's Application for Local Planning and Community Accessibility (ALPACA).
dataIdInfo.idCredit: ACS (American Community Survey), US Census, WSDOT - Public Transportation Division

dataLineage.statement: The 2015 update (produced 2/7/17) to the 2012 ALPACA tool. US Census 2011-2015 American Community Survey (ACS) data were linked to the 2015 Census TIGER county shapefile.

prcStep.stepDesc: ACS data tables were downloaded from American FactFinder (https://factfinder.census.gov). A python script was developed to process raw data and calculate summaries and percentages. The data was then joined to a US Census Bureau 2015 TIGER county shapefile in ArcMap 10.3.1.

report.measDesc: Data was acquired from the US Census Bureau and was assumed to be published with minimal error. All processing conducted by WSDOT was quality assured but error cannot be ruled out.
The data only includes information collected from the US Census Bureau pertaining to the states of Washington, Oregon, and Idaho. Other states and countries have not been included.
